Removed Ratt album listing. Article states new tracks for 2019, does not specify album. In the age of Spotify, many bands are releasing singles without albums. Need an article to say definitively that they are planning an album for 2019.
Removed good faith listings of non-notable album where neither the artist or the album have a Wikipedia article. Create one or both as a start before listing it again.
[[MOS:ITALICTITLE]] vs [[MOS:MINORWORK]].  Albums are italicized, songs get double quotation marks.
Added a producer for Lana del Rey's new album

Removed genres for Aimyon album as original research. Not supported by citation, and there is no album article to support the genres.  Band genre is insufficient for listing album genre. Removed genre listing for Beyooooonds album as original research. Removed genre for Empire album as not supported. A genre was listed in album article, but was unsupported/speculative, so was removed. Cannot be listed on this list as not proven.

Removed publisher Wikipedia link from inside citation. Keeping citations clean, one link, to the citation. Inside a sentence in an article, it is useful to reference the source, but there is never a need in a citation to link to an article about the source.

The album article has articles showing song notability, but nothing promoting album notability.
